row.Content:
In Acumatica ERP, you can define classes and attributes for flexible, meaningful classification of leads, contacts, opportunities, business accounts, cases, and marketing campaigns with respect to your business.{br}

A class is a group of records, such as leads or cases, that shares at least one common characteristic.{br}

An attribute is a quality or characteristic (for instance, age or industry) that gives your company specific information that is helpful for its business.{br}

For each class, you can define a list of attributes to gather class-specific information about the records of that class.{br}

In this chapter, you will find information about the classes used for leads, contacts, opportunities, business accounts, cases, and campaigns.

row.column:
You can use the following forms to define classes for leads, contacts, opportunities, business accounts, cases, and marketing campaigns:[anchor|#_6a0a0ec3-9929-486e-8bd6-4b5458e1e698] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR207000|CR207000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_50_00|Contact Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR205000|CR205000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_90_00|Opportunity Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR209000|CR209000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_80_00|Business Account Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR208000|CR208000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_60_00|Case Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR206000|CR206000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_25_00|Campaign Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR202500|CR202500])
==Use of Attributes== For each class, you can define a list of attributes to gather class-specific information about the records that belong to that class.{br}
The [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_00|Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306000|CR306000]), and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_20_00|Marketing Campaigns] ([~/?ScreenId=CR202000|CR202000]) forms have tabs reserved for attributes. If you select a class when creating a new record, the attributes of that class appear on the respective tab of the entry form.((({S:Hint}To keep classification meaningful, you should always enter proper values for attributes, both for those marked as required and for optional ones. ))) If you specify values for the attributes of a business account and then convert the business account to a customer or vendor account, the resulting account retains these attributes. If the customer or vendor class to which the resulting account belongs also has attributes specified, these attributes are added to the list of attributes of the resulting account.{br}
You can use attributes on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_15|Approval Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205015|EP205015]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205010|EP205010]) forms to specify the criteria for assigning records to the appropriate owners.{br}
For more information about the use of attributes in Acumatica ERP, see [HelpRoot_Administration\CS__con_Attributes|Attributes]. ==Example of Lead Classes and Attributes== Consider an example that uses classes and attributes for leads. ((({S:Hint}Attributes and classes are used similarly for leads, contacts, opportunities, business accounts, cases, and marketing campaigns. ))) Imagine that you sell two products, one for resale by retailers and the other for direct corporate use. You handle many leads and would like to divide them into groups based on whether they are related to a retail store or to a corporation. You can create two classes for these leads: [anchor|#_2e586e63-b4a3-4346-8f0c-80098ecb69e4] *One class, called ''Retail'', for leads associated with retail stores of various sizes: This class might contain an attribute called '''Size''' with the values ''Small'', ''Midsize'', and ''Big'' corresponding to the store size, as well as other attributes to give you additional information about these stores. *Another class, called ''Corporate'', for leads associated with organizations that are final consumers: Because some organizations may be tax-exempt, you might define an attribute called '''Tax Status''' with two possible values, ''Tax-exempt'' and ''Taxable''. Another attribute, '''Company Type''', might have such values as ''Corporation'', ''Hospital'', ''University'', and ''School''.
When you enter a new lead on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, you should select a lead class on the '''CRM Info''' tab. Once the class is selected, its attributes appear on the '''Attributes''' tab. After that you can enter specific attribute values for the lead. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_20_50_00|Attributes] ([~/?ScreenId=CS205000|CS205000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR207000|CR207000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_50_00|Contact Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR205000|CR205000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_90_00|Opportunity Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR209000|CR209000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_80_00|Business Account Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR208000|CR208000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_60_00|Case Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR206000|CR206000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_25_00|Campaign Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR202500|CR202500]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_00|Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306000|CR306000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_20_00|Marketing Campaigns] ([~/?ScreenId=CR202000|CR202000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_15|Approval Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205015|EP205015]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205010|EP205010])

Acumatica ERP gives you the ability to distribute the workload among employees. You can use assignment maps to assign records, such as leads or cases, to the appropriate users. This topic describes the general rules that you can follow when creating assignment maps.{br}
In Acumatica ERP, it&rsquo;s easy to base assignment rules on company policies because records can be distributed among workgroups or individual employees in an almost unlimited number of ways, based on the properties and attributes of the records being distributed. For example, leads can be distributed by location: leads with postal codes starting with ''94'' can go to Workgroup 1, leads with postal codes starting with ''95'' can go to Workgroup 2, and so on. As another example, distribution of cases based on geographical territories can be determined by phone area codes. Records can also be distributed alphabetically or by another condition, or they can be distributed by multiple criteria, based on the values of properties and attributes of the record. {br}
You create the maps for automatic assignment of records by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205010|EP205010]) form. If you want to use workgroups in an assignment map, before you start creating the map, make sure that all workgroups involved in the processing of the records are represented on the company tree. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_61|Company Tree] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204061|EP204061]) form, add the required workgroups and specify their members and default owners. For more information on the company tree, see [HelpRoot_Organization\EP__con_Company_Organizational_Chart|Company Tree and Workgroups]. {br}{TOC} ==Assignment Rules== An assignment map may include any number of rules, which are executed sequentially. A rule in an assignment map includes conditions and actions to be performed if the conditions are met.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] form, in the '''Rules''' pane, you create a list of rules. For each rule, you specify conditions for executing the rule. If a condition or rule is no longer required in an assignment map, you can temporarily deactivate it by clearing the '''Active''' check box in the settings of that condition or rule on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] form. A deactivated rule is marked with the '''(Inactive)''' prefix in the '''Rules''' pane. ==Assignment Conditions== To use record properties and attributes in assignment conditions in the '''Conditions''' pane on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] form, you select the appropriate entities (types of records) first.{br}
Conditions, which are specified for each rule, are based on the values of the properties and attributes of the records. The properties are specified on the data entry form used to create the record. For the classes that are used to group the records, particular attributes can be configured; users can specify the attribute values for the individual records (such as leads) on the data entry form used to create the records.{br}
If your company&rsquo;s policies require that all records of a particular type (such as cases) should be distributed, then before you start creating an assignment map, you should draw a diagram for your conditions to ensure that they are complete. Consider the previous example of assignment rules based on the first two digits of the postal code: If you expect most leads to have postal codes starting with ''94'' and ''95'', do not forget to add a rule for distributing leads whose postal codes start with numbers other than ''94'' or ''95''. {br}
Rules should divide records of a particular type into non-intersecting sets. If rules allowed the same records to be assigned to two or more groups, all assignments would be performed in the workgroup or individual employee that is mentioned higher in the list of rules, and the records would never reach the second workgroup or employee. ==Rule Application== Once the assignment maps are created, you can select the default maps for cases, leads, contacts, business accounts, and opportunities by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form. These maps are used during the mass assignment processes that you can perform through the following forms:[anchor|#ul_jqc_hgw_q3] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_10|Assign Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503010|CR503010]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_11|Assign Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503011|CR503011]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_33_10|Assign Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503310|CR503310]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_31_10|Assign Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503110|CR503110]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_32_10|Assign Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503210|CR503210])
Once a record is assigned to a workgroup, the default owner of the group is assigned as the owner of the item. If no owner is specified for the group, the record is considered to be assigned to the workgroup. Members of the same workgroup can view records assigned to the group or to an employee from the group.{br}
You can change the owner of the record manually by using the entry form for that record. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Organization\EP__con_Assignment_Automation|Managing Assignment and Approval Maps] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_20_50_00|Attributes] ([~/?ScreenId=CS205000|CS205000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_00|Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306000|CR306000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_61|Company Tree] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204061|EP204061]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205010|EP205010])

A lead is a potential customer, a person or a company, that expresses an interest in the products the organization offers. Assigned employees contact and process leads. Acumatica ERP provides flexible tools that can be used by sales teams for effective lead management; these tools can be adjusted to any lead qualification procedure that is used in your organization.{br}{TOC} ==Learning Objectives== From reading the topics in this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#ul_dmx_2lv_pr] *Create new leads *Qualify a lead *Convert a lead to an opportunity
==Applicable Scenarios== A lead is created in Acumatica ERP and then reviewed, rated, and qualified by a marketing manager or automatically. After that, a sales manager may accept the lead as a sales opportunity, return the lead to the marketing team for nurturing, or disqualify it and exclude it from further marketing and sales activities. ==Ways of Creating Leads in Acumatica ERP== In Acumatica ERP, you can register leads in any of the following ways:[anchor|#_198b3605-08f7-4d82-965b-08a3fa711784] *By manually entering a lead on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form. For step-by-step instructions on registering a lead manually, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__HOW_To_Create_a_Lead|To Create a Lead]. *By creating a lead from Acumatica add-in for Outlook based on the details of the selected email recipient or sender. For detailed instructions, see [HelpRoot_Integration\OU__how_To_Create_Lead|To Create a Lead by Using the Acumatica Add-In]. *By using import scenarios to import lists of leads on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_60_36|Import by Scenario] ([~/?ScreenId=SM206036|SM206036]) form. For instructions on how to import such a list by using a previously configured import scenario, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__HOW_To_Import_Leads|To Import Leads by Using an Import Scenario]. *By enabling integration with web services on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_70_40|Web Services] ([~/?ScreenId=SM207040|SM207040]) form for automatic import of leads *By activating the functionality of incoming mail processing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_02|System Email Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=SM204002|SM204002]) form for automatic creation of leads based on sender information
==Contact Information== On the '''Contact Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, you can specify the name, contact information, and address of the lead. Also, this tab holds information about the lead's consent to the processing of personal data if the ''GDPR Compliance Tools'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. (For details about GDPR compliance tools, see [HelpRoot_Administration\GD__MNG_Handling_Personal_Data|Handling Personal Data].){br}
If the '''Override''' check box on the '''Contact Info''' tab is cleared, the contact information of the lead is synchronized with the contact information of the related contact, business account, and opportunity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]), and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) forms. If the check box is selected, the contact information for the selected lead on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form can differ from the contact information of the related record on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts], [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts], and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] forms, as well as from the contact information of the leads related to this lead. The synchronization or overriding of settings applies to all the settings on the '''Contact Info''' tab. ==Related Entities== In Acumatica ERP, multiple leads may be linked to one business account or contact. On the '''Leads''' tabs of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) and the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) forms, you can see all the leads linked to a business account or contact, respectively.{br}
A lead that is being nurtured by a marketing team may receive marketing newsletters and other mailings. By using the '''Marketing Lists''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, you can see all marketing lists the lead is subscribed on. For more information about marketing lists, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__con_Marketing_Lists|Marketing Lists].{br}
On the '''Campaigns''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form, you can view a list of all marketing campaigns where the lead is included as a member. For details about campaigns in Acumatica ERP, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__con_Campaigns|Marketing Campaigns].{br}
The '''Opportunities''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form includes all opportunities linked to the lead. For detailed information about opportunities, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Opportunities|Managing Opportunities].{br}
On the '''Activities''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form, you can work with all the activities related to the lead, including current, completed, and planned activities. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__con_Managing_Your_Tasks__Events__and_Activities|Managing Tasks, Events, and Activities]. ==Lead States== As a lead is being processed by marketing and sales teams, it progresses through various states, each of which is represented by a status displayed in the '''Status''' box in the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form. The '''Status''' box is non-editable. Transitions between lead states can be performed through actions on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form.{br}
In Acumatica ERP, a lead may be assigned one of the following statuses:[anchor|#_1ca7576a-94aa-4557-8028-1759086504dd] *''New'': The lead has been created but no work has been done on it yet. *''Open'': The lead is being qualified by a marketing team. *''Sales-Ready:'' The lead has been qualified by a marketing team as showing more interest in the organization&rsquo;s products than other leads. *''Sales-Accepted'': The lead has been initially reviewed and accepted by the lead qualification team and it is ready to meet with the sales team for further qualification. *''Converted:'' The lead has been qualified and converted to an opportunity. For a lead with this status, most of the boxes on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form are read-only; you can only edit the value in the '''Description''' box in the Summary area. *''Disqualified'': The lead is showing no interest in the organization&rsquo;s products or is not reachable (for example, the contact information is not valid). This status may also be used for duplicate leads. For more information about finding duplicates among CRM records in Acumatica ERP, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__con_Duplicate_Validation|Validating Records for Duplicates].
If a lead has the ''New'', ''Open'', ''Sales-Ready'', or ''Sales-Accepted'' status, the '''Active''' check box on the '''CRM Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form is selected by default to indicate that the lead can be nurtured by a marketing team. The system clears the check box if the lead has the ''Converted'' or ''Disqualified'' status.{br}
You can use the following actions to transition a lead between states:[anchor|#_178c2cae-d421-4ab0-add0-a63207964f06] *'''Open''': Opens the '''Details''' dialog box, where you select the reason for opening the lead and confirm the action. The status of the lead will be changed for ''Open''. The action is available when the status of the lead record is ''New'', ''Sales-Ready'', ''Sales-Accepted'', ''Converted'', or ''Disqualified''. *'''Qualify''': Opens the '''Details''' dialog box, where you select the reason for qualifying the lead and confirm the action. The status of the lead will be changed for ''Sales-Ready''. The action is available when the status of the lead record is ''New'' or ''Open''. *'''Accept''': Opens the '''Details''' dialog box, where you select the reason for accepting the lead and confirm the action. The status of the lead will be changed for ''Sales-Accepted''. The action is available when the status of the lead is ''New'', ''Open'', or ''Sales-Ready''. *'''Disqualify''': Opens the '''Details''' dialog box, where you select the reason for disqualifying the lead and confirm the action. The status of the lead will be changed for ''Disqualified''. The action is available, if the status of the lead record is ''New'', ''Open'', ''Sales-Ready'', or ''Sales-Accepted''. *'''Convert to Opportunity''': Opens the '''New opportunity''' dialog box, where you can enter initial data that is required to create an opportunity. By using that dialog box, you can create a new contact and business account for the lead, if needed, or review existing ones. The action is available, if the status of the lead record is ''New'', ''Open'', ''Sales-Ready'', or ''Sales-Accepted''.
A system administrator can configure notifications related to lead states. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Notifications_About_Changes|Notifications About Changes on Data Entry Forms]. ==Lead Processing Workflow== The following diagram illustrates the lead processing workflow.[anchor|#_8ab38508-4799-4d98-bb04-ab231d78c20b][image:UserGuide/Images/CRM_Lead_Processing_Flow.png|popup|450px]

Lead nurturing is the process of working with leads that are not yet ready to buy. Acumatica ERP provides tools that enable you to nurture leads more effectively, and as a result, to increase lead conversion to opportunities.{br}

When working with leads, you can register all your activities in the system to save all information you get. For each lead, you can create tasks and activities and schedule events. You can configure a dashboard to show the list of your current tasks and events.{br}

By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_40|Event and Task Categories] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204040|EP204040]) form, you can create a list of event and task categories and provide a color code for each category.{br}

You can filter leads by specific properties and add them to mailing lists and campaigns so that you can send personalized emails by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_80_00|Mass Emails] ([~/?ScreenId=CR308000|CR308000]) form. {br}

As leads progress through different statuses, Acumatica ERP lets you easily access all related information, which is available on '''Relations''' tabs on each form included in the lead management workflow. Also, at every change of the lead status, you can use the '''Reason''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form to specify the reason for that change.{br}

Review lead records periodically to find leads that were not qualified as opportunities or for some reason have proved to be of no value to your company. Such records can be disqualified; as a result, their status will be changed to ''Disqualified''. To update leads in bulk, use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_20|Update Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503020|CR503020]) form.
