row.Content:
In the following sections, you will find details about marketing reports that you can use to analyze lead sources, lead processing and campaign-related metrics.{br}

 Acumatica ERP provides the following forms designed for marketing and sales personnel to monitor multiple marketing metrics and track marketing goals:[anchor|#_0b6815f5-6586-4fb1-884f-de1a3652fd62]
*''Leads BI (CR3010BI)''
* ''Lead Conversion BI (CR3011BI)''
* ''Campaign Summary (CR2020BI)''
* ''Campaign Sales Orders (CR203010)''
* ''Campaign Invoices (CR203000)''

You can access the Acumatica ERP marketing reports in the '''Inquiries''' and '''Reports''' categories of the '''Marketing''' workspace.{br}

The marketing reports data are displayed in inquiry forms and pivot tables. You can build other pivot tables as filter tabs, filter data by any column in a pivot table depending on the information that you would like to obtain, or configure dashboards using this data.{br}{TOC}

row.column:
''Campaign Summary (CR2020BI)'' inquiry form, based on the ''Campaign Summary'' generic inquiry displays a list of marketing campaigns with statistical information on each campaign, including the following details:[anchor|#_bce73fb7-241e-4f9c-8d5a-b9351b42abff] *The campaign ID *The planned budget *The expected return *The number of converted leads *The lead conversion rate *The won opportunities value
With this information, you can view the outcome of converted leads by campaign and monitor the values for money of each campaigns. The ''Campaign Sales Orders (CR203010)'' generic inquiry form displays a list of marketing campaigns and related the sales orders, including the following details:[anchor|#_1c732a7a-683c-4e65-a307-9bd6a7fcb3ad] *The campaign ID *The number of a sales order *The status of a sales order *The total amount of a sales order *The name of the customer
You can use this report to calculate the revenue affected by a campaign.{br}
The ''Campaign Invoices (CR203000)'' generic inquiry form displays a list of marketing campaigns associated with invoices, including the following details:[anchor|#_67dd0e70-7e85-4a7f-88cc-c8a113153f93] *The campaign ID *The number of an invoice *The status of an invoice *The total amount of an invoice *The name of the customer
You can use this report to calculate the revenue affected by a campaign.{br}{TOC}

row.Content:
In the following sections, you will find details about support reports that you can use to analyze case processing and productivity-related metrics for a support team.{br}

 Acumatica ERP provides the following forms designed for customer service managers to monitor multiple case-processing metrics and track customer support goals and for customer service representatives to track their individual and team performance:[anchor|#_0b6815f5-6586-4fb1-884f-de1a3652fd62]
*''Cases BI (CR3010BI)''
* ''Support Activities (CR3061BI)''

You can access the Acumatica ERP support reports in the '''Inquiries''' and '''Reports''' categories of the '''Support''' workspace.{br}

The support reports data are displayed in inquiry forms and pivot tables. You can build other pivot tables as filter tabs, filter data by any column in a pivot table depending on the information that you would like to obtain, or configure dashboards using this data.{br}{TOC}
